-- Asian Stocks Advance After Greece’s Parliament Approves Austerity Measures
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2012-02-13T02:08:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/asian-stocks-advance-after-greek-parliament-approves-austerity-measures.html
Asian stocks advanced as the Greek
parliament approved austerity measures to help secure a second
bailout package.  The MSCI Asia Pacific Index rose 0.2 percent to 125.05 at
11:04 a.m. in  Tokyo  after briefly erasing losses as the Hong
Kong market opened. Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index
rose 0.4 percent. The  Hang Seng Index  rose 0.2 percent after
falling as much as 0.5 percent earlier.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
